sec.p:
Atlantic wolffish use their strong jaws to eat hardshell mollusks, crustaceans, and echinoderms. They do not eat other fish. They are known to frequently eat large welks ( Buccinum), cockle (bivalve) (Polynices, Chrysodomus and Sipho), sea clams ( Mactra), large hermit crabs, starfish, sea urchins and green crabs (
Carcinus maenas
). They are an important predator of sea urchins and green crabs, whose populations escalate rapidly and can negatively effect the health of a marine system. 9
